wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.def: Rural population refers to people living in rural areas as defined by national statistical offices. It is calculated as the difference between total population and urban population. Aggregation of urban and rural population may not add up to total population because of different country coverages.
wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.name: Rural population
wdi2-SP.RUR.TOTL.source: World Bank staff estimates based on the United Nations Population Division's World Urbanization Prospects: 2018 Revision.
